mponent.\n9. `apps/mobile/app/components/VisualBackground.vue` — background component.\n10. Wire: `apps/mobile/app/assets/css/main.scss` — import tokens.scss, add VisualBackground to app.vue or layouts.\n\nWait — main.scss currently has its own `:root` with different colors (--bg #0e0f12, --accent #7c5cff lilac-ish). The visual-foundation says canonical --bg #0D0F17, --magic #B9A7FF fixed. I need to reconcile. main.scss currently defines tokens inline. The packet says raw hex ONLY in tokens.scss + fallback. So I should move token definitions to tokens.scss and have main.scss import it. But main.scss has body styles etc. \n\nAllowed to touch main.scss \"ONLY to wire the tokens + background\". So: create tokens.scss with canonical definitions, import from main.scss via `@use` or `@import`. Replace the `:root` block in main.scss to import tokens instead. Keep body/layout rules in main.scss.\n\nBut careful: existing pages use `--accent`, `--accent-grad`, `--accent-2`, `--glow-accent`, `--ring`, `--error`, `--ok`, `--shadow-card`. If I change tokens, existing P10 pages may break visually but typecheck still passes. The packet says \"No full visual redesign of already-built pages beyond foundation contracts.\" So I should keep backward-compatible alias names where pages use them, OR accept that P10 pages get restyled. Since P10 pages use --accent-grad etc., and the new foundation doesn't define --accent-grad... \n\nHmm. The packet scope: \"No full visual redesign of already-built pages beyond foundation contracts.\" But also visual-foundation §4 canonical tokens don't include --accent-grad/--accent-2/--glow-accent/--ring/--error/--ok. To avoid breaking P10, I'll keep those legacy aliases in tokens.scss too (they're raw hex / derived) — actually that's fine, tokens.scss is THE token file. I'll define canonical tokens per spec, plus keep the existing app-utility tokens (accent-grad, ring, error, ok, glow) so P10 pages still compile and render. Mark legacy ones with ponytail