"Мои задачи\" → --task-list-heading\n- level_up_text: \"Новый уровень!\" → --level-up-text\n- empty_state_text: \"Пока пусто\" → --empty-state-text\n\nCSS vars for text? Text content can't be a CSS var directly (content: var(--x) works for pseudo-elements). For real text, the component reads from visual_state. So mapper returns text vars as CSS custom properties AND the component reads visual_state for actual text. The packet says \"covering color fields AND the TEXT fields ... as text vars\". So expose them as --task-button-text etc. Components can use `content: var(--task-button-text)` for decorative, or read from state object. I'll expose them as vars (string values) — usable in CSS `content`. Good enough for foundation.\n\nbackground_variant → --bg-variant token (or sets --bg overlay). card_variant → --surface override. profile_background → --profile-bg. decorative_detail → --decor-detail. accent_color → --accent.\n\nMap variants to canonical colors:\n- background_variant dark-ember/deep-forest/midnight → keep --bg canonical (fixed), but maybe slight tint. Spec says background_variant is a \"background token set\". To avoid raw hex outside tokens, I'll map to named tokens defined in tokens.scss. E.g. dark-ember → --bg-ember, deep-forest → --bg-forest, midnight → --bg-midnight (all defined in tokens.scss). Mapper sets --bg to the chosen one? But --bg is fixed canonical per spec §4. Hmm spec §4 lists --bg as fixed canonical #0D0F17. But VisualState.background_variant exists. Conflict? \n\nvisual-foundation §10: \"background_variant -> background token set\". So background_variant selects a set of background tokens (tints). The fixed --bg stays; variant adds an overlay/tint layer. I'll implement: mapper sets --bg-variant to a token name (defined in tokens.scss with raw hex), and VisualBackground uses it. --bg itself stays canonical. That keeps \"raw hex only in tokens.scss\".\n\nSimplify: mapper returns:\n- --accent: state.accent_color (validated against catalog; if not in catalog, fallback to default)\n- --bg-variant: token name for background tint\n- --card-variant: token name for card surface tint\n- --profile-bg: token name\n- --decor-detail: state.decorative_detail\n- text vars\n\nAnd tokens.scss defines the tint tokens (--bg-dark-ember etc.) with raw hex.\n\nAccent validation: catalog {#7dd3fc,#a7f3d0,#f9a8d4,#fde68a}. If state.accent_color not in catalog → fallback default (--blue #7EA7FF? or first catalog?). Spec says backend catalog is those 4. Frontend should trust backend but validate to avoid injection. I'll validate; if invalid, use fallback default. Default fallback accent: pick --blue (#7EA7FF) — canonical, non-lilac. Actually one of catalog is more \"realistic\". I'll default to #7dd3fc (sky). Fine.\n\nNow scatter.ts: given decorative_detail, return fixed array of {x%,y%,rotation,scale,asset} positions. NO Math.random. Keyed by detail. ~6-8 positions per detail. Self-check: same input → same output (reference equality / JSON stable).\n\nLet me write the plan and call critic.\n\nLet me draft files mentally then call critic on plan. Let me write plan to a scratch variable (internal). I'll call critic now.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Got full context. Now drafting plan and running critic on it."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_78dec06f6f55447e9b2ddcad","name":"Agent","arguments":{"subagent_type":"critic","description":"Critic P09-1 plan","max_turns":100,"prompt":"You are the plan critic for RLM packet P09-1 (visual foundation) in repo /usr/projects/Диплом. depth=complex.\n\nPROJECT_RULES (excerpt):\n- Files ≤150 LOC production (docs exception).\n- Backend = source of truth; frontend NO Math.random() for visual/accent; no final_xp/level/roll_value/foreign user_id in client payloads.\n- Raw hex ONLY in tokens.scss + fallback theme file.\n- Vue SFC v-bind() in styles OK.\n- No Google Fonts CDN / external icon sets. Local assets only.\n- VisualState type already in shared/contracts/visual-settings.ts with fields: accent_color, background_variant, card_variant, task_button_text, task_list_heading, profile_background, decorative_detail, level_up_text, empty_state_text.\n- Settings type has disable_visual_randomness, reduced_motion.\n- Existing committed P09/P10 must NOT be reverted. P10 mobile pages use legacy CSS vars: --accent, --accent-grad, --accent-2, --glow-accent, --ring, --shadow-card, --error, --ok, --surface, --surface-2, --bg, --text, --muted, --safe-*.\n- Canonical tokens (visual-foundation.md §4): --bg #0D0F17, --surface #181B25, --surface-2 #222635, --stroke #30364A, --text #F4F0E8, --muted #9EA7B8, --magic #B9A7FF (FIXED brand), --mana #8FD7C7, --xp #F6C76B, --blue #7EA7FF, --danger #FF6B7A. --accent is RUNTIME from VisualState.accent_color; backend catalog {#7dd3fc,#a7f3d0,#f9a8d4,#fde68a} (NO lilac).\n- OD1 (lilac in catalog) / OD2 (scatter seed) are separate backend edits — MUST NOT add them.\n\nALLOWED WRITE PATHS: shared/visual/**, apps/mobile/app/assets/**, apps/mobile/app/components/Logo.vue, apps/mobile/app/components/VisualBackground.vue, apps/mobile/app/assets/css/tokens.scss, and MAY touch apps/mobile/nuxt.config.ts / apps/mobile/app/app.vue / apps/mobile/app/assets/css/main.scss ONLY to wire tokens + background. Must NOT touch shared/api/**, shared/contracts/**, backend, admin, P10 auth pages.\n\nACCEPTANCE gates: rg Math.random (none in apps/shared visual), rg fonts.googleapis|gstatic (none), rg raw hex only in tokens/fallback/asset-meta, mapper has self-check runnable via `npx tsx`, `cd apps/mobile && bun run typecheck` passes, brand assets copied locally.\n\nTASK TEXT (P09-1): Add visual foundation — tokens SCSS, VisualState→CSS-vars mapper (with text fields + fallback), brand asset registry (7 local assets copied), deterministic scatter helper, Logo.vue + VisualBackground.vue components, wire into app.\n\nPLAN DRAFT:\n\n=== Files to create ===\n\n1. apps/mobile/app/assets/css/tokens.scss  (~110 LOC)\n   - :root block with ALL canonical color tokens (raw hex ONLY here).\n   - Semantic aliases: --brand-decoration-primary -> var(--magic) etc (no raw hex, use var()).\n   - Runtime --accent default = #7dd3fc (fallback, non-lilac, from catalog).\n   - Legacy app-utility tokens kept so P10 pages don't break: --accent-grad (linear-gradient(var(--magic), var(--blue))), --accent-2 -> var(--blue), --glow-accent, --ring, --shadow-card, --error -> var(--danger), --ok -> var(--mana). Defined via var() references, no new raw hex.\n   - Non-color hierarchy: --radius-sm/md/lg/xl, --space-*, --font-sans (local stack, NO google), --surface-opacity-*, --shadow-soft, --motion-fast/med, --safe-top/bottom/left/right (env()).\n   - Background/card/profile variant tint tokens: --bg-dark-ember/--bg-deep-forest/--bg-midnight, --card-graphite/--card-pine/--card-plum, --profile-quiet-grid/--profile-night-lines/--profile-calm-shapes (raw hex tints, only here).\n   - ponytail: comment marking legacy utility aliases kept for P10 compat.\n\n2. apps/mobile/app/assets/brand/  (copy 7 assets)\n   - chubzik-logo.png (from logo.png)\n   - magic-spark.svg, magic-curl.svg, magic-orbit.svg, magic-thread.svg, magic-wisp.svg, tiny-spark.svg\n   - SVGs already aria-hidden + currentColor. Verified.\n\n3. shared/visual/assets.ts  (~35 LOC)\n   - export BRAND_ASSETS = { logo: {name:'chubzik-logo.png', alt:'Чубзик'}, magicSvgs: ['magic-spark',...6 names] }\n   - export function brandAssetUrl(name): string  — returns relative path '~/assets/brand/'+name (Nuxt resolves). Or just export paths. Keep simple: export const LOGO_ASSET, MAGIC_SVG_ASSETS list.\n   - No DOM, pure data.\n\n4. shared/visual/scatter.ts  (~95 LOC)\n   - type ScatterItem = { x:number; y:number; rotation:number; scale:number; asset:string }\n   - export function scatterLayout(detail: VisualState['decorative_detail']): ScatterItem[]\n   - Fixed LAYOUT_TABLE: Record<detail, ScatterItem[]> with ~6 items each, hardcoded positions (percentages), rotations, scales, asset names from registry.\n   - NO Math.random. Deterministic. Pure function.\n   - Self-check: demo()/__main__ block using `if (import.meta.url...)` — actually use `if (process.argv[1] === fileURLToPath(import.meta.url))` pattern with asserts: same input twice → JSON equal; no Math.random import.\n   - Self-check runnable: `npx tsx shared/visual/scatter.ts`.\n\n5. shared/visual/visual-state.ts  (~120 LOC)\n   - import type { VisualState, Settings } from '../contracts/visual-settings'\n   - export const FALLBACK_VISUAL_STATE: VisualState (stable dark defaults: accent_color #7dd3fc, background_variant 'midnight', card_variant 'graphite', profile_background 'calm-shapes', decorative_detail 'soft-sparks', Russian text defaults).\n   - export const ACCENT_CATALOG = ['#7dd3fc','#a7f3d0','#f9a8d4','#fde68a'] as const\n   - export function visualStateToCssVars(state: VisualState | null, settings?: Pick<Settings,'disable_visual_randomness'|'reduced_motion'> | null): Record<string,string>\n     - If state null OR settings.disable_visual_randomness → use FALLBACK_VISUAL_STATE.\n     - Validate accent_color ∈ ACCENT_CATALOG; else fallback accent.\n     - Return map: --accent, --bg-variant, --card-variant, --profile-bg, --decor-detail, --task-button-text, --task-list-heading, --level-up-text, --empty-state-text, --reduced-motion ('1'|'0').\n     - No raw hex except the catalog constant + fallback accent (which are in this file — acceptable as \"fallback theme file\").\n   - Self-check: demo() assert block runnable via `npx tsx shared/visual/visual-state.ts`: (a) null → fallback vars present, (b) valid state → accent propagated, (c) invalid accent → fallback accent, (d) disable_visual_randomness → fallback, (e) deterministic (call twice → deep equal).\n\n6. shared/visual/index.ts  (~5 LOC) — re-export assets, scatter, visual-state.\n\n7. apps/mobile/visual.ts  (~3 LOC) — `export * from '../shared/visual'` (mirrors apps/mobile/api.ts pattern → importable as `~~/visual`).\n\n8. apps/mobile/app/components/Logo.vue  (~70 LOC SFC)\n   - Props: size (number|string, default 48), color (string, default 'currentColor'), glow (boolean), decorative (boolean, default true → aria-hidden).\n   - Uses PNG as CSS mask: -webkit-mask url(brand/chubzik-logo.png) center/contain no-repeat; background: var(--logo-color, currentColor).\n   - v-bind in <style> for size/color/glow.\n   - aria-hidden when decorative. role=\"img\" + aria-label when not decorative.\n\n9. apps/mobile/app/components/VisualBackground.vue  (~90 LOC SFC)\n   - Renders fixed full-screen div with magic SVG decor via mask, low opacity, aria-hidden.\n   - Uses scatter.ts layout keyed by --decor-detail var (read from CSS var via getComputedStyle? No — better: read from a prop `decorativeDetail` passed by parent, OR read --decor-detail CSS var). Decision: component takes optional prop `decorativeDetail?: VisualState['decorative_detail']` default 'soft-sparks'; renders scatterLayout(detail) items as positioned <span> masks of the SVGs.\n   - Uses CSS var --decor-detail to switch layout via data-attribute? Simpler: prop drives layout. Parent (app.vue) reads visual_state from store (later P10 wiring) — for now default fallback.\n   - respects reduced-motion: if --reduced-motion var = '1' or prefers-reduced-motion media query → disable transitions/glow.\n   - respects disable_visual_randomness: layout still deterministic (already is), but reduce opacity/motion to least-dynamic via --reduced-motion var.\n   - SVGs rendered as mask images referencing ~/assets/brand/*.svg, color via currentColor → token color.\n   - aria-hidden on whole background.\n\n=== Wiring edits ===\n\n10. apps/mobile/app/assets/css/main.scss\n    - Replace the existing `:root { ... }` block with `@use './tokens.scss';` (or `@import`). Keep body, focus-visible, .display, .text-grad, .tap, a rules. Remove raw hex from main.scss (now in tokens.scss). Legacy vars --accent-grad etc now live in tokens.scss.\n\n11. apps/mobile/app/app.vue\n    - Wrap NuxtLayout/NuxtPage in a relative container, add <VisualBackground /> as first child (fixed, behind content). Keep existing script minimal. ~10 LOC edit.\n\n=== NOT doing ===\n- Not touching shared/api, shared/contracts, backend, admin, P10 auth pages.\n- Not adding OD1 lilac / OD2 scatter seed.\n- Not adding new VisualState fields.\n- No Math.random anywhere.\n- No Google Fonts.\n\n=== Acceptance plan ===\n- `npx tsx shared/visual/scatter.ts` and `npx tsx shared/visual/visual-state.ts` → asserts pass.\n- `cd apps/mobile && bun run typecheck` → passes.\n- rg Math.random apps shared → none (self-check uses assert, not random).\n- rg fonts.googleapis|gstatic → none.\n- raw hex only in tokens.scss + visual-state.ts (catalog/fallback) + assets (svg paths).\n\nReturn exactly one JSON object, no markdown, no prose:\n{\"ok\":bool,\"feedback\":string,\"phase\":\"plan\"}\n\nfeedback:\n- empty string if there are no medium/high/critical issues\n- one issue per line\n- format: [medium|high|critical]rule @loc → fix\n- drop low severity and nits\n- max 8 issues"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"polza","model":"z-ai/glm-5.2","usage":{"input":3876,"output":4669,"cacheRead":38656,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47201,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782864827547,"responseId":"gen_2183390358387036161"},"timestamp":"2026-07-01T00:15:09.328Z","cwd":"/usr/projects/Диплом"}
